      "name": "Do I have to disclose flood risk when selling a property in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Flood affectation is a material fact under Queensland property law. Sellers and agents are legally obligated to disclose known flood risk. The Brisbane City Council flood overlay data is publicly available, so attempting to conceal it creates significant legal exposure."
